  "management45": "Critical operational constraints are flagged at 23 airports right now. No engine anti-ice operations are currently flagged. Across base airports: 7 critical, 11 high, 8 medium, 13 normal. Key bases needing attention include London Luton (LTN/EGGW), London Gatwick (LGW/EGKK) and Katowice Wojciech Korfanty (KTW/EPKT); plus 15 other bases. 8 additional base airports are at medium severity and should be monitored closely. At base airports, the dominant pattern is snow-related runway contamination risk, mist and low cloud base  — most notably around Bucharest Henri Coandă (OTP/LROP), Gdańsk Lech Wałęsa (GDN/EPGD) and Modlin (WMI/EPMO). Network hotspots: Berlin Brandenburg Willy Brandt (BER/EDDB), Lennart Meri Tallinn (TLL/EETN), Turku (TKU/EFTU), Billund (BLL/EKBI), Copenhagen Kastrup (CPH/EKCH) and 18 others. Primary drivers: low cloud base, snow / blowing snow and mist. Expected impact is reduced runway capacity with higher delay and diversion risk, especially where visibility/RVR and cloud base are very low. Since the last update, 12 airports changed status, led by Gdańsk Lech Wałęsa (GDN/EPGD), Solidarity Szczecin–Goleniów (SZZ/EPSC), Olsztyn-Mazury (SZY/EPSY) and 9 others.",
